values:
Brian Creeper Wiley joined forces with Paul to tr and creep on me while we were headed down, brian sent me crazy stalker texts about wanting to date me and when i was like 'sorry i have a boyfriend' he said 'oh well do you wanna do down to panama city beach with me and talk about jesus?' CREEPS.
i promise you its not.


RANDOMS

we stayed @ Edgewater Resort on the beach which was b-e-a-utiful.
rachel and i had horrid first impressions of each other but after becoming roomies and sharing the master bedroom we inevitably became BFFS and now i adore her so so much :-D
Joshyface likes to take a bajillion pictures with me.

on the beachhh @ sharkys
in the hot tub @ edgewater. [paul knows hes unphotogenic and cant handle his beautiful face being unperfectly captured the wrong way by a camera lens.] ps: idk what josh is doing
paul josh and i went through a lot of scheming to get rachel to our room right @ 620 on monday for her surprise bday party and it was definitely difficult but we pulled it off :-) this is afterwards..dennis and jan had girl questions so i whipped out taylors cosmo.






OUR WARRIORS PREPARING FOR BATTLE


TRYING TO DEFEAT MSU. [however we were the evil team so we had to lose.]
POST SPIRITUAL BATTLE


cute things for the boys HOWEVER the boys were better at being cute:


getting ready for our dateee

dinner @ hooks okay so, the weather was not permitting for a beach date, so i got a phone call from andy telling us to stay in our rooms...then we heard a knock and brady escorted us in his minivan to J's room, when we pulled up we werent allowed to open the doors..boys were standing there with roses and they each escorted one of us and handed us a rose, we walked up the stairs and into the dark room where candles lit the doorway and derek and brian were taking our shoes off. the floor was covered in white sheets, pillows and rose petals..then i looked over to the counter and saw the boysss





they served us each these plates with massive amounts of desserts on them.
yes andy serenaded us with a song they had written for us entitled 'such a blessing' and YES it made us cry.
the 3 people i spent the most time with. the neighbor, the BFF and the neighbors friend. yes thats what josh is.
you know, 24 hour road trip back home... opportune photoshoot. the end. ps: theres more on FBOOK :-D
